Source-code compatibility shims required by the Gradle dependency-override
approach in patch/9.3.overrides.gradle. These changes adapt Elasticsearch
source files to API additions in the bumped libraries that the init script
forces (resolutionStrategy.eachDependency cannot patch source code).

Currently:
  - log4j 2.19.0 -> 2.25.4 adds Logger#getFlowMessageFactory(), which the
    custom Logger implementation NoOpLogger must override.

diff --git a/x-pack/plugin/core/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/core/security/support/NoOpLogger.java b/x-pack/plugin/core/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/core/security/support/NoOpLogger.java
--- a/x-pack/plugin/core/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/core/security/support/NoOpLogger.java
+++ b/x-pack/plugin/core/src/main/java/org/elasticsearch/xpack/core/security/support/NoOpLogger.java
@@ -928,9 +928,14 @@
     @Override
     public <MF extends MessageFactory> MF getMessageFactory() {
         return null;
     }
 
+    @Override
+    public org.apache.logging.log4j.message.FlowMessageFactory getFlowMessageFactory() {
+        return org.apache.logging.log4j.message.DefaultFlowMessageFactory.INSTANCE;
+    }
+
     @Override
     public String getName() {
         return null;
     }
